1
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:15,951
You are the last man
whom I could ever marry!

2
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:20,247
Do you think any consideration would
tempt me? Your arrogance, your conceit,

3
00:01:20,372 --> 00:01:23,333
and your selfish disdain
for the feelings of others!

4
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:28,255
My opinion of you was decided when I heard
Mr. Wickham's story of your dealings with him.

5
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:31,758
Well at least in that I may defend myself.

6
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:36,471
Could you expect me to rejoice
in the inferiority of your connections?

7
00:01:36,597 --> 00:01:42,144
To congratulate myself on the hope of relations
whose condition in life is so below my own?

8
00:01:43,145 --> 00:01:45,314
You are mistaken, Mr. Darcy.

9
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:50,569
Your declaration merely spared me
the concern I might have felt in refusing you,

10
00:01:50,694 --> 00:01:53,780
had you behaved in a more
gentleman-like manner.

11
00:01:54,197 --> 00:01:55,824
Who's there, Fitzwilliam?

12
00:01:57,075 --> 00:02:00,954
- Darcy! We'd quite despaired of you!
- Is that my nephew?

13
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:05,417
Where have you been?
Let him come in and explain himself!

14
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:08,629
No. You will forgive me.

15
00:02:09,588 --> 00:02:13,342
- You'll forgive me.
- Darcy, you are unwell?

16
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:18,889
I'm very well, thank you, but I have a pressing
matter of business. You'll forgive me.

17
00:02:19,014 --> 00:02:21,808
Make my apologies to Lady Catherine, Fitzwilliam.

18
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,462
To Miss Elizabeth Bennet.

19
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:59,262
Be not alarmed, madam, on receiving this letter,

20
00:02:59,388 --> 00:03:02,808
that it contain any repetition
of those sentiments or offers

21
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:06,728
which were this evening so disgusting to you.

22
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:18,824
But I must be allowed to defend myself
against the charges laid at my door.

23
00:03:18,949 --> 00:03:21,284
In particular those relating to Mr. Wickham,

24
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:25,914
which if true, would indeed be grievous,
but are wholly without foundation,

25
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:31,294
and which I can only refute by laying before you
his connection with my family.

26
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:40,512
Mr. Wickham is the son of a very respectable
man, who had the management of our estates.

27
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:45,142
My own father was fond of him
and held him in high esteem.

28
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,773
We played together as boys.

29
00:03:56,027 --> 00:04:00,866
After his father's early death, my father
supported him at school and at Cambridge,

30
00:04:00,991 --> 00:04:03,952
and hoped he would make the church
his profession.

31
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:12,127
But by then George Wickham's habits were
as dissolute as his manners were engaging.

32
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:23,722
My own excellent father died five years ago.

33
00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:27,809
His attachment to Mr. Wickham
was to the last so steady,

34
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:31,938
that he desired that a valuable family living
might be his as soon as it was vacant.

35
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:35,567
Mr. Wickham declined
any interest in the church as a career,

36
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:41,239
but requested, and was granted,
the sum of 3,000 pounds instead of the living.

37
00:04:44,868 --> 00:04:50,624
He expressed an intention of studying the law.
I wished, rather than believed him to be sincere.

38
00:04:53,585 --> 00:04:54,920
Thank you.

39
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:01,009
I'm most exceedingly obliged.

40
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:06,348
All connection between us
seemed now dissolved.

41
00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:10,519
Georgiana.

42
00:05:16,024 --> 00:05:18,819
Being now free from all restraint,

43
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:22,364
his life was one of idleness and dissipation.

44
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:26,409
How he lived, I know not.

45
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:32,082
But last summer our paths crossed again,
under the most painful circumstances,

46
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,835
which I myself would wish to forget.

47
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:40,173
My sister, Georgiana,
who is more than ten years my junior,

48
00:05:40,298 --> 00:05:44,219
was left to the guardianship
of Colonel Fitzwilliam and myself.

49
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:49,808
About a year ago,
she was taken from school to Ramsgate,

50
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:55,480
and placed in the care of a Mrs. Younge, in whose
character we were most unhappily deceived.

51
00:05:56,523 --> 00:06:00,277
And thither also went Mr. Wickham,
undoubtedly by design.

52
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:07,284
She was persuaded to believe herself in love,
and to consent to an elopement.

53
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:10,704
She was then but fifteen years old.

54
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:18,753
A day or two before the intended elopement,
I joined them unexpectedly.

55
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:39,649
Unable to support the idea of grieving a brother
whom she looked up to almost as a father,

56
00:06:39,774 --> 00:06:42,485
she acknowledged the whole plan to me
at once.

57
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:45,947
You may imagine what I felt and how I acted.

58
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:49,951
Mr. Wickham left the place immediately.

59
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,458
Come.

60
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:07,761
Mr. Wickham relinquished his object, which was
of course, my sister's fortune of 30,000 pounds.

61
00:07:09,054 --> 00:07:13,016
A secondary motive must have been
to revenge himself on me.

62
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:16,770
Had he succeeded, his revenge
would have been complete indeed.

63
00:07:17,395 --> 00:07:23,193
This, madam, is a faithful narrative
of all my dealings with Mr. Wickham.

64
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:16,830
You do look pale, Lizzy.
Why don't you have some breakfast?

65
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:20,542
- I'm sure it will do you good.
- I am well, Charlotte.

66
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:24,546
I've stayed indoors too long.
Fresh air and exercise is all I need.

67
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:27,632
The woods around Rosings are so beautiful
at this time of year.

68
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,889
Miss Bennet!

69
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,809
Mr. Darcy.

70
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:23,354
I've been walking the grove some time
in the hope of meeting you.

71
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:26,941
Will you do me the honor of reading this letter'?

72
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:47,629
This, madam, is a faithful narrative
of my dealings with Mr. Wickham,

73
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:51,883
and for its truth I can appeal
to the testimony of Colonel Fitzwilliam,

74
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:54,385
who knows every particular of these transactions.

75
00:09:54,511 --> 00:09:58,264
I know not under what form of falsehood
Mr. Wickham imposed himself on you,

76
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:00,600
but I hope you'll acquit me
of cruelty towards him.

77
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:04,479
I found that I'd better not meet Mr. Darcy.

78
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:07,398
Scenes might arise,
unpleasant to more than myself.

79
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:12,821
The other charge leveled at me, is that
regardless of the sentiments of either party,

80
00:10:12,946 --> 00:10:15,615
I detached Mr. Bingley from your sister.

81
00:10:16,491 --> 00:10:21,538
I have no wish to deny this, nor can I blame
myself for any of my actions in this matter.

82
00:10:26,668 --> 00:10:31,089
I had not long been in Hertfordshire
before I saw that Bingley admired your sister,

83
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:35,969
but it was not until the dance at Netherfield
that I suspected a serious attachment.

84
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:41,099
His partiality was clear, but though she received
his attentions with pleasure,

85
00:10:41,224 --> 00:10:44,519
I did not detect any symptoms
of peculiar regard.

86
00:10:45,353 --> 00:10:50,150
The serenity of her countenance convinced me
that her heart was not likely to be easily touched.

87
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,569
Insufferable presumption!

88
00:10:52,694 --> 00:10:57,073
I did not wish to believe her to be indifferent.
I believed it on impartial conviction.

89
00:10:57,198 --> 00:10:58,992
Very impartial!

90
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:02,579
You've missed the two gentlemen!
They came to take their leave!

91
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:03,746
Mr. Darcy came here?

92
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:08,585
He went away directly,
but the Colonel waited for you over half an hour!

93
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,503
Now they are gone abroad!

94
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:13,548
I dare say we shall be able to bear
the deprivation.

95
00:11:27,478 --> 00:11:33,067
As to my objections to the marriage, the
situation of your family, though objectionable,

96
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:38,615
was nothing in comparison with the total want of
propriety so frequently betrayed by your mother,

97
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:42,785
your younger sisters,
and even occasionally your father.

98
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:51,753
That will do extremely well, child.
You have delighted us long enough.

99
00:11:52,629 --> 00:11:55,298
Now there will be a great marriage!

100
00:11:56,132 --> 00:12:01,137
And you know, that will throw the girls
into the paths of other rich men!

101
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:12,815
My friend left Netherfield for London
on the following day.

102
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:18,988
There I pointed out to him the certain evils of
his choice of your sister as a prospective bride.

103
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:22,659
It was not difficult to convince him
of your sister's indifference to him.

104
00:12:22,784 --> 00:12:25,662
I cannot blame myself for having done thus much.

105
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:29,082
For destroying all her hope of happiness?

106
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:32,043
Yes, I'm sure you do not blame yourself.
Hateful man!

107
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:37,423
There is but one part of my conduct in the affair
on which I do not reflect with satisfaction.

108
00:12:37,548 --> 00:12:38,800
Really? Astonish me.

109
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:42,303
That I concealed from him
your sister's being in town.

110
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,144
Perhaps this concealment was beneath me.

111
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,564
It was done, however, for the best.

112
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:57,652
On this subject I have nothing more to say,
and no other apology to offer.

113
00:12:58,152 --> 00:12:59,821
Insufferable!

114
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:03,658
- Lizzy!
- Charlotte, we will be late!

115
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:05,493
Lizzy!

116
00:13:07,495 --> 00:13:13,293
I have endeavored to count the times
Lady Catherine has invited us since your arrival.

117
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:16,296
I believe it may be as many as ten invitations!

118
00:13:16,421 --> 00:13:19,215
- Eleven, counting this one!
- Eleven!

119
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:25,138
There! You have indeed been favored
with peculiar condescension.

120
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:28,766
- Do you not agree, Miss Elizabeth?
- Oh... yes!

121
00:13:28,891 --> 00:13:31,602
How could anybody think otherwise?

122
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:35,690
And this is your last invitation,
on this visit, at least.

123
00:13:35,815 --> 00:13:38,318
It is truly a very cruel deprivation.

124
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:42,363
I hardly know how I shall bear
the loss of Lady Catherine's company.

125
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,033
You feel it keenly!

126
00:13:45,742 --> 00:13:49,162
Yes, of course you do, my poor young cousin.

127
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:56,502
They were such fine young men,
and so particularly attached to me!

128
00:13:56,627 --> 00:14:01,424
They were excessively sorry to go,
but so they always are!

129
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:05,928
The dear Colonel rallied his spirits tolerably,

130
00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:10,224
but Darcy seemed to feel it most acutely.

131
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:15,188
His attachment to Rosings certainly increases.

132
00:14:18,316 --> 00:14:22,111
You are very dull this evening,
Miss Elizabeth Bennet.

133
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:27,200
You have scarce spoke two words together.
Are you so out of spirits?

134
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:32,121
- No indeed, madam.
- Of course you are, to be going away yourself.

135
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:37,794
Who indeed would not be sad to be deprived
of Rosings, and indeed of the gracious...

136
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:41,631
You will write to your mother
and say you wish to stay longer.

137
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:44,967
She could certainly spare you
for another fortnight.

138
00:14:45,093 --> 00:14:47,470
But my father cannot.

139
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:50,056
He wrote last week to hurry my return.

140
00:14:50,181 --> 00:14:54,519
Your ladyship is very kind, but I believe
we must leave as planned on Friday.

141
00:14:54,644 --> 00:14:57,855
Your father may spare you if your mother can.

142
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:01,109
Daughters are never of much consequence
to a father.

143
00:15:01,234 --> 00:15:05,488
And if you will stay another month complete,

144
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:10,618
it will be in my power to take you
as far as London myself, in the Barouche box.

145
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:17,166
For I cannot bear the idea of two young women
traveling post by themselves.

146
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,794
It is highly improper!

147
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:23,965
I am excessively attentive to all those things.

148
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:27,385
My uncle is to send a servant for us
when we change to the post.

149
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:34,392
Your uncle! He keeps a manservant, does he?

150
00:15:35,268 --> 00:15:39,689
I'm very glad you have somebody who thinks of
these things. Where will you change horses?

151
00:15:39,814 --> 00:15:42,191
- At Brom...
- Bromley, of course.

152
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:46,195
Mention my name at the Bell
and they will attend you.

153
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:48,406
Your ladyship is very kind.

154
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:53,411
Indeed, we are all infinitely indebted
to your ladyship's kindly bestowed solicitude...

155
00:15:53,536 --> 00:15:57,832
Yes, yes, but this is all extremely vexing!

156
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,127
I'm quite put out.

157
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:05,465
What are you doing? I thought the trunks
went outside before breakfast.

158
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:11,387
Lady Catherine was so severe about the only
right way to place gowns, that I couldn't sleep,

159
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:14,015
and I am determined to start afresh!

160
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,642
Maria, this is your trunk, these are your gowns.

161
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:21,898
You may arrange them in any way you wish.
Lady Catherine will never know!

162
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:25,818
My dear sister,
you will have much to tell your father...

163
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,653
Bring that one round here.

164
00:16:38,873 --> 00:16:40,541
Well, cousin...

165
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:44,128
you have seen for yourself now
the happiness of our situation.

166
00:16:44,879 --> 00:16:49,050
Our intimacy at Rosings is a blessing
of which few could boast.

167
00:16:49,175 --> 00:16:52,470
- Indeed they could not.
- Indeed.

168
00:16:53,346 --> 00:16:55,264
Now you have seen our felicity.

169
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:59,936
Perhaps you may think
your friend has made a very fortunate alliance.

170
00:17:00,061 --> 00:17:01,771
Perhaps more so than...

171
00:17:03,231 --> 00:17:07,985
- But on this point it will be as well to be silent.
- You are very good.

172
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:13,533
Only let me assure you that I can,
from my heart,

173
00:17:13,658 --> 00:17:17,870
most cordially wish you equal felicity in marriage.

174
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:21,666
Charlotte and I have but one mind
and one way of thinking.

175
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:26,212
We seem to have been designed for each other!

176
00:17:48,025 --> 00:18:06,877
How much I shall have to conceal.

177
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:21,350
You must allow me to tell you
how ardently I admire and love you.

178
00:18:44,332 --> 00:18:45,666
Lizzy!

179
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,960
Lizzy!

180
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:59,722
To see your faces when you looked up!

181
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:03,643
- You didn't expect we'd come to meet you.
- No, we did not.

182
00:19:03,768 --> 00:19:09,690
There! ls not this nice? Cold ham and pork
and salads and every good thing!

183
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:14,320
We mean to treat you, but you must
lend us money, we spent ours. Look!

184
00:19:14,445 --> 00:19:15,529
It's not pretty,

185
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:19,075
- but I thought I might as well buy it as not.
- It's vile, isn't it?

186
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:24,163
- Very ugly. What possessed you to buy it?
- There were two or three much uglier.

187
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:27,792
I shall pull it to pieces
and see if I can make it up any better.

188
00:19:29,043 --> 00:19:34,507
It doesn't signify what anyone wears, for the
regiment will be at Brighton the whole summer!

189
00:19:34,632 --> 00:19:36,092
Our hearts are broken!

190
00:19:36,217 --> 00:19:39,595
We want papa to take us all to Brighton
for summer but he will not.

191
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:44,141
- I'm glad to hear it.
- Shouldn't you like to go to Brighton?

192
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:46,435
- I should not.
- She would.

193
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:50,981
She would love it, when she hears the news
about a certain person we all know.

194
00:19:51,399 --> 00:19:54,527
- Shall we tell her?
- Yes, and watch to see if she blushes!

195
00:19:56,070 --> 00:20:00,116
- You may go. We'll call if you're needed again.
- Very good, miss.

196
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:08,249
Wickham is not to marry Mary King after all!

197
00:20:08,374 --> 00:20:11,877
She's been taken away by her uncle to Liverpool
and Wickham is safe!

198
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,715
Perhaps we should say Mary King is safe.

199
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:19,135
Was there a very strong attraction between them,
do you think'?

200
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:23,389
Not on his side! I shouldn't think
he cared three straws about her.

201
00:20:23,514 --> 00:20:29,145
Who could about such a nasty freckled little thing?
Don't look at me like that, Lizzy!

202
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:32,565
I know you think as ill of her as I do.
Pass the celery, Kitty.

203
00:20:32,690 --> 00:20:36,944
Aren't you glad we came to meet you?
It'll be merry on the journey home.

204
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:41,949
- Kitty, you're squashing my bandbox!
- You should have put it on the roof!

205
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:47,288
- If you didn't lollop about there'd be room for us all.
- I don't lollop, you do!

206
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:53,502
Mr. Darcy proposed! I can scarce believe it!

207
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:57,631
Not that anyone's admiring you
should be astonishing.

208
00:20:57,757 --> 00:21:02,052
But he always seemed so severe,
so cold, apparently.

209
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:07,016
And yet he was in love with you all the time!
Poor Mr. Darcy.

210
00:21:07,141 --> 00:21:09,685
I cannot feel so much compassion for him.

211
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:14,356
He has other feelings which will soon drive away
any regard he felt for me.

212
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:20,488
- You do not blame me for refusing him?
- Blame you? Oh, no.

213
00:21:22,573 --> 00:21:25,826
But you do blame me for speaking
so warmly of Wickham?

214
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:31,707
No. How could you have known about his
vicious character? If indeed he was so very bad.

215
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:37,463
But I cannot believe Mr. Darcy would fabricate
such a dreadful slander,

216
00:21:37,588 --> 00:21:40,132
involving his own sister too.

217
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:43,427
No, it must be true.

218
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:49,308
- Perhaps there has been some terrible mistake.
- No, Jane. That won't do!

219
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,727
You'll never be able to make them both good!

220
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:56,816
There is just enough merit between them
to make one good sort of man.

221
00:21:56,941 --> 00:22:00,903
And for my part I'm inclined to believe
it's all Mr. Darcy's.

222
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:03,239
Poor Mr. Darcy.

